[This article leaves some uncertainty about the percentage of the cases
described that are truly typhoid fever. It is also unclear whether the
ciprofloxacin resistance described is a reflection of proper microbiological
characterization of antimicrobial susceptibility, or of clinical failures
in cases that may or may not be correctly diagnosed. The Widal test is a
serological test for antibodies against the O and H antigens of _Salmonella_
sp. The article is correct that fecal and blood cultures are required to
confirm the
diagnosis. - Mod.ES
.....................................es/jw
